reviews.text: The worse club I have EVER danced at! I traveled from Las Vegas To dance In this town not knowing what I was getting into. They make you check your phone in the front and put it in a plastic bag, if you needed to make a call you have to go all the way out the building and they give you a time limit and then there was roach on the manager back, the dances are $5 , there’s no stage , the dressing room is a cage box with nothing in it , they just had bags all over the place, dirty bathroom and roaches on the wall. If I’m lying I’m dying. I would rate 0 star if I could.

This place is a hit or miss!  Went there about 12pm got a rib sandwich, I believe it was yesterday ribs they were dry, barely had any meat on them, the ribs looked old. My coworker even said they looked old. The little bit of meat that was on the bone you had to really pull off the bone because it was dry to the bone. The end piece they gave me was extremely dry to to the point it was stringy. This is about the second or third time this has happened thats why I said it's a hit or miss spot. I really try to support black business but if they are going to serve the black community like that then I'll have to go somewhere else.

The ribs are perfectly tender & flavorful & the wings are insanely good. They serve whole wings not party wings so you get your monies worth! Great sauce & sides too. The only thing I would change would be more variety in the drinks. The neighborhood is a tad rough & the place itself is retro, but that's actually what makes going a unique experience. Don't judge--just enjoy! Highly recommended!
Travel from out of Town, club showed me and I made good money. It was worth the money, time, travel I invested.

I went there on a monday night, and for 14$ to get in before 10 pm. its a good bang for your buck. The dancers, are on point, and the food is excellent. Theres plenty of security in the establishment,  it feel like a safe environment for the area it's in. My only complaint, are the expensive horrible drinks. My advice is drink a bottle in the car before you go in

Green beans were nothing but mush as were the sweet potatoes. and the French fries were old and dry  not cooked on the day of the order.
The chicken breast and catfish were fresh and were the only 2 things we could eat so we paid just under $50 for half a meal from the Shetiff Road location. Will never order from them again.

I was completely surprised when I first came to the location but later left feeling great about the service and food received! Was looking for one near a location and this one came up! The customer service was great and the food was tasty! When they ask if you want seasoning on top, Say yes and get extra! Game Changer!!!

Ordered 16 wings they were good, they pretty much forced fries on me although I didn't want them he said they come with it so I just took them, the fries were small not much to brag about but I liked the wings.

I’m a frequent customer to Hip Hop Fish & Chicken and yes they have made small mistakes with me before but this was a major one that they refuse to take accountability for!!! The cashier charged me double for my order and when I showed the charges to him on my bank statement, he refused to give me a refund!! What led to an argument ended with him finally giving my refund. I recommend going to another location or paying with cash because this was absolutely outrageous.
Sooooo good. Much better than expected. Not greasy nor heavy. Huge portions for the money. Can’t wait to come back for that HipHop Seasoning!

We visited on their first Friday at dinner service and enjoyed ourselves. They’re still working out some kinks with speed of service BUT the food and drinks were both awesome and a great price. Because one of the items we ordered was slow they gave us complimentary hush puppies and ice cream for the kids. Great hospitality. Definitely coming back!

I think Oasiz is great and has the potential to be amazing. It is in the Cheverly neighborhood that is void of restaurants, so this is a welcome addition to the area. Food is good and there are many selections of drinks. There is room for improvement so I will be happy to give a fifth start at a later date.

Definitely a hidden spot. Clean black owned bar and grill. Excellent customer service and fresh quick good food. The chicken cheese steak was torch. Fresh crispy fries. Will be back for other items on the menu to try. Catfish nuggets was a recommendation from the cook.

i have worked in the area for nearly 40 years.  used to eat here when it was Friendly Inn.  we are in a food desert and doing a search for restaurants just for the heck of it, oasiz popped up.  had lunch there today (wednesday), asked when they opened....monday, 2 days ago!  place is well decorated, friendly staff and the cheyenne red burger and onion rings are excellent.  i hope they have heat, it was a bit chilly.  i wish them much success.

Friendly customer service, cozy atmosphere.

Had a wonderful cocktail, seriously the whiskey sour was amazing. My wife loved her margarita and my friend loved her long island. Will definitely come back.

name: Rincon Escondido Deli Bar and Restaurant

reviews.text: We left happy! I ordered a mojito, it had fresh mint and good amount of rum… delicious! I also ordered the bean and cheese papusas… bomb / the chicken baleandos… yummy yummy! / Honduran fried chicken was extra crispy, but I must admit my favorite part of the chicken was the slaw and the plantain chips piled around it. The only thing I would change are the complimentary chips and salsa. Chips were stale and salsa was super thin and lacked flavor. Overall, I’d definitely stop here again and just say hold the chips.
Tried the Honduran fried chicken today was delish es as was their “sopa de mondongo” very yummy can’t wait to be back

Do Not Stop Here To Eat
Gross food . Weak drinks. Rude Staff
Very NEGATIVE place . We left the drinks n the food it was that bad.

they're a family business and they make different kinds of tacos. From my understanding, it has Honduras touch to it. I'm coming back again because they have good customer service and super willing to communicate with Deaf people. They sell drinks as well and they got TVs.

My husband and I ate here tonight. I had a delicious shrimp dish and my husband had the fajitas. The only negative was the margarita I ordered tasted like bottled margarita mix -- and was $14! There were no prices on the drink list...

Healthy Fresh Meals is a prepared meal distributor that has both delivery and local pickup of preordered meals.  The product is consistently fresh, wholesome and delicious.  When our schedules get tight, having meals ready in our fridge proves to be a lifesaver.  I highly recommend.

Inconspicuous location with potholed parking, but warm reception and good food with a home cooked feel inside. Don't judge a culinary book by its cover. Stop by and try it. The yuca frita con chicharron was particularly tasty. Small menu, but competently prepared. A true diamond in the rough.

I dropped by and ordered tacos and pupusas for Carryout. All were fresh and tasty. They did not speak English much but that is no barrier to ordering deliciousness.
FYI Neighbor car detailing business rudely got annoyed at me parking in front of his place, so I moved 2 spots over.
We got there less than five minutes before they closed They were so nice and made us these wonderful tacos. Every time I’m on that side of town I make it a point to go and have lunch there.

This place makes GREAT FOOD. So Delicious. Authentic Hispanic Flavoring. Authentic Hispanic Preparation. Place is very small and offers take out only but...WOW...So good. A DIVE for sure but do not let the outside fool you. Go inside and order anything. You will be happy with your meal. Very reasonable prices too. Can also call ahead and have it ready when you get there.
Good taco’s and very nice people 👍🏻
